The paper introduces a new information-theoretic strategy for designing a quality metric of projections in Projection Pursuit, which is a common technique in machine learning and data visualization. The paper also discusses two specific examples of this strategy, one of which is related to Principal Component Analysis (PCA), a popular technique in machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
